156.2	Gold_standard	Gold standard	The gold standard is a monetary system in which the standard economic unit of account is a fixed weight of gold. There are distinct kinds of gold standard. First, the gold specie standard is a system in which the monetary unit is associated with circulating gold coins, or with the unit of value defined in terms of one particular circulating gold coin in conjunction with subsidiary coinage made from a lesser valuable metal.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6f/Goldkey_logo_removed.jpg/220px-Goldkey_logo_removed.jpg
